    "severity": "critical",
    "description": "Removed integer overflow protection in base64_encode(). On 32-bit systems where size_t is 32-bit, the calculation (insize + 2) / 3 * 4 + 1 can overflow when insize > UINT_MAX/4. This causes malloc() to be called with a wrapped-around small value instead of the required large buffer size, resulting in a heap buffer overflow when encoding large inputs. An attacker can trigger this with large base64 inputs to corrupt heap memory.",
    "fix_patch": "--- a/lib/base64.c
+++ b/lib/base64.c
@@ -199,6 +199,11 @@ static CURLcode base64_encode(const char *table64,
   if(!insize)
     insize = strlen(inputbuff);

+#if SIZEOF_SIZE_T == 4
+  if(insize > UINT_MAX/4)
+    return CURLE_OUT_OF_MEMORY;
+#endif
+
   base64data = output = malloc((insize + 2) / 3 * 4 + 1);
   if(!output)
     return CURLE_OUT_OF_MEMORY;
"
  },
  {
    "file": "lib/cookie.c",
    "line": 147,
    "severity": "high",
    "description": "Incorrect array index in cookie domain boundary check. The function cookie_tailmatch() is used to verify that a hostname matches a cookie domain according to RFC 6265. The change removed the -1 offset from the boundary check, causing the code to verify the wrong character position. The code now checks if hostname[hostname_len - cookie_domain_len] (the first character of the matched domain) is a dot, instead of checking hostname[hostname_len - cookie_domain_len - 1] (the character before the domain match). Since domain names never start with a dot, this causes all legitimate subdomain matches to fail. This breaks cookie domain matching and prevents valid cookies from being sent with requests.",
    "fix_patch": "--- a/lib/cookie.c
+++ b/lib/cookie.c
@@ -144,7 +144,7 @@ static bool cookie_tailmatch(const char *cookie_domain,
    */
   if(hostname_len == cookie_domain_len)
     return TRUE;
-  if('.' == *(hostname + hostname_len - cookie_domain_len))
+  if('.' == *(hostname + hostname_len - cookie_domain_len - 1))
     return TRUE;
   return FALSE;
 }
"
  }
]

